The article announces several appointments in the US government. Donald R. Cravins is set to become the Under Secretary of Commerce for Minority Business Development. Rebecca Lee Haffajee will be the new Assistant Secretary of Health and Human Services, replacing Richard G. Frank. David P. Pekoske will take on the role of Administrator of the Transportation Security Administration for a five-year term. Lastly, Hugo F. Rodriguez, Jr. will serve as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Nicaragua.